      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When photons hit Photosystem II, they excite electrons that travel down an electron transport chain, pumping protons into the thylakoid lumen to create a gradient that drives ATP synthase. This process also reduces NADP+ to NADPH as electrons move from Photosystem I through ferredoxin to the NADP+ reductase complex. Essentially, light energy is converted into chemical potential energy stored in the proton gradient and then in the high-energy electrons of NADPH.",
